---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Contacts from "../components/Contacts.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
import Directions from "../components/Directions.astro";

import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import { Icon } from "astro-icon/components";

// Pictures
import Cessna150_1 from "../assets/photos/cessna-150m/1.jpg";
import Cessna150_2 from "../assets/photos/cessna-150m/2.jpg";
import Cessna150_3 from "../assets/photos/cessna-150m/3.jpg";
import Cessna150_4 from "../assets/photos/cessna-150m/4.jpg";
import Cessna150_5 from "../assets/photos/cessna-150m/5.jpg";
// Avionics
import Cessna150_Avionics_1 from '../assets/photos/cessna-150m/avionics/1.png';

const layoutProps = {
  title: "Book Cessna 150M at Corona Municipal Airport with Cloud 9 Aviation",
  description: "Two-seat airplane for training, adventures, or hours building."
};

const airplane = {
  name: "Cessna 150M",
  tailNumber: "N8590U",
  wetRate: 145,
  usefulLoad: 2295,
};

---

<Layout {...layoutProps}>
  <Header />
  <section class="pb-6 max-w-6xl mx-auto">

    <div class="flex justify-between items-center p-6">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold">Cessna 150M</h1>
      <a class="flex items-center gap-2 font-bold" target="_blank" href={"https://registry.faa.gov/aircraftinquiry/Search/NNumberResult?NNumbertxt=" + airplane.tailNumber}>{airplane.tailNumber}<Icon name="mdi:open-in-new" /></a>
    </div>

    <!-- <div class="px-6 grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 items-start"> -->
    <!-- Aircraft Image -->
    <div class="px-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
      <!-- Left / main image -->
      <div class="col-span-2">
        <Image
          src={Cessna150_1}
          alt="Cessna 150M N8590U"
          class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow"
        />
        <a href="#contacts">
          <button class="btn btn-primary mt-4 w-full bg-sky-600 border-sky-600"
            >Reserve this Aircraft</button
          >
        </a>
      </div>

      <!-- Right / stacked images -->
      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 hidden sm:flex">
        <Image
          src={Cessna150_3}
          alt="Cessna 150M Photo 3"
          class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow"
        />
        <Image
          src={Cessna150_5}
          alt="Cessna 150M Photo 5"
          class="w-full h-auto rounded-lg shadow"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-3 px-6 gap-4 grid">
      <div class="col-span-2">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Overview</h2>
        <p class="py-4">
          The Cessna 150M aircraft rental is a two-seat, single-engine,
          high-wing airplane that has long been a favorite for flight training,
          pilot instruction, and time building. Known for its reliability,
          easy handling, and economical operating costs, this Cessna 150 rental
          is an excellent choice for student pilots, hour-building pilots,
          and recreational flying within a professional flight club environment.
        </p>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Features</h2>
        <ul class="py-4">
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:currency-usd" /><strong>Wet Rate:</strong> $145/hr</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:seat" /><b>Seating Capacity:</b> 2 (Pilot and one passenger)</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:engine" /><b>Engine:</b> Continental O-200-A, 100 horsepower</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:speedometer" /><b>Maximum Cruise Speed:</b> Approximately 124 knots (143 mph)</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:map-marker-distance" /><b>Range:</b> Around 420 nautical miles</li>
          <!-- <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:gauge" /><b>Avionics:</b> Basic VFR instrumentation, with options for upgrades</li> -->
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:gas-station" /><b>Fuel Capacity:</b> 26 gallons (usable)</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:weight" /><strong>Useful Load:</strong>2.295 lbs </li>
          <!-- <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:gauge" /><strong>Flight Display:</strong> Dual Garmin G5 (with synthetic vision)</li> -->
          <!-- <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:gauge-empty" /><strong>Primary NAV/COM:</strong> Garmin GNC-355 (WAAS)</li> -->
          <!-- <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:gauge-full" /><strong>Secondary NAV/COM:</strong> Garmin GNC-255</li> -->
          <!-- <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:audio-input-stereo-minijack" /><strong>Audio Panel:</strong> Garmin GMA-345</li> -->
          <!-- <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:gauge-low" /><strong>Engine Monitor:</strong> JP1-730</li> -->
          <!-- <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:radio-tower" /><strong>Transponder:</strong> GTX 327 (Mode C)</li> -->
          <!-- <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:radio" /><strong>ADS-B:</strong> Out</li> -->
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:ruler" />Wingspan: 33 feet 4 inches</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:ruler" />Length: 23 feet 11 inches</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:ruler" />Height: 8 feet 6 inches</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:weight" />Empty Weight: Approximately 1,100 pounds</li>
          <li class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 light:odd:bg-sky-100 dark:even:bg-gray-600"><Icon name="mdi:weight" />Maximum Takeoff Weight: 1,600 pounds</li>
        </ul>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold">Equipment & Avionics</h2>
        <p class="py-4">
          The Cessna 150M is equipped with standard VFR instrumentation,
          including an airspeed indicator, altimeter, vertical speed indicator,
          and basic navigation equipment. While it is primarily designed for
          visual flight rules, the aircraft can be outfitted with additional
          avionics for enhanced navigation and communication capabilities.
        </p>
        <div>
          <!-- Avionics Equipment #1 -->
          <h3 class="text-md font-bold">Dual Garmin G5 Flight Display</h3>
          <div class="sm:flex">
            <Image
              src={Cessna150_Avionics_1}
              alt="Cessna 150M Photo 2"
              class="w-auto sm:w-1/3 h-auto rounded-lg shadow mb-4"
            />
            <div class="px-4">
              <p>Enhance your flight experience with the dual Garmin G5 flight displays, providing clear and intuitive navigation and instrument information.</p>
              <ul class="text-xs list-disc list-inside mt-2">
                <li><strong>Synthetic Vision Technology:</strong> Clear-3D terrain view.</li>
                <li><strong>Altitude indicator:</strong> Digital, easy to read.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Avionics Equipment #2 -->
          <h3 class="text-md font-bold">Dual Garmin G5 Flight Display</h3>
          <div class="sm:flex">
            <Image
              src={Cessna150_Avionics_1}
              alt="Cessna 150M Photo 2"
              class="w-auto sm:w-1/3 h-auto rounded-lg shadow mb-4"
            />
            <div class="px-4">
              <p>Enhance your flight experience with the dual Garmin G5 flight displays, providing clear and intuitive navigation and instrument information.</p>
              <ul class="text-xs list-disc list-inside mt-2">
                <li><strong>Synthetic Vision Technology:</strong> Clear-3D terrain view.</li>
                <li><strong>Altitude indicator:</strong> Digital, easy to read.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
          <!-- Avionics Equipment #3 -->
          <h3 class="text-md font-bold">Dual Garmin G5 Flight Display</h3>
          <div class="sm:flex">
            <Image
              src={Cessna150_Avionics_1}
              alt="Cessna 150M Photo 2"
              class="w-auto sm:w-1/3 h-auto rounded-lg shadow mb-4"
            />
            <div class="px-4">
              <p>Enhance your flight experience with the dual Garmin G5 flight displays, providing clear and intuitive navigation and instrument information.</p>
              <ul class="text-xs list-disc list-inside mt-2">
                <li><strong>Synthetic Vision Technology:</strong> Clear-3D terrain view.</li>
                <li><strong>Altitude indicator:</strong> Digital, easy to read.</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </div>
      <!--
      <div>
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-800 pt-5 my-2">Location</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-600 mb-4">
          Based at Corona Municipal Airport (KAJO).
        </p>
        <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-lg overflow-hidden">
          <iframe
            class="w-full h-96 border-0"
            src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d8141.388053071811!2d-117.60822502358232!3d33.89606427321625!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x80dcc9005bb6c065%3A0x6b6a128f0bbdbc7b!2sCloud%209%20Aviation!5e1!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1768011495751!5m2!1sen!2sus"
            allowfullscreen=""
            loading="lazy"
            referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"
          ></iframe>
        </div>
      </div>
      -->
      <Directions />

    </div>
    <!--
      <h2>Equipment & Avionics</h2>
      <p>Standard equipment includes a basic VFR cockpit with a single-axis autopilot, and avionics can be upgraded to include modern GPS and transponder systems.</p>
    -->
  </section>
  <Contacts />
  <Footer />
</Layout>
